data.name: tb_helpText.Text
data.value:
There are 4 Types of Conditions you can use: #IF This is used, if the specified condition is true #MIF This is used, if the specified conditions are true (2-3 Conditions) #Otherwise This is used, if no other condition is true #End This is used, when the countdown ran out (overwriting #Otherwise)
To express different Time Values use: %s Seconds %S Seconds (always two digits) %m Minutes %M Minutes (always two digits) %h Hours %H Hours (always two digits) %a AM/PM Display (requieres 24h to be disabled)
You can use the following search types: = the value has to be exacty that < the value has to be smaller > the value has to be lager
You can use the following in between different conditions in a Multi-Condition: | one of the two conditions have to be true & both conditions have to be true
You can search for the following values: seconds minutes hours
It works from top to bottom, so only first Condition to be true is beeing used. Invalid IF- & MIF-Conditions are ignored. Please note that a Multi-Condition with 3 Values is connected like this: (val1 &/| val2) &/| val3
